\f0\fs28 \cf0 An early worry of lockdown and furlough was that a massive increase I home internet usage \'96 particularly video calls and streaming \'96 would cripple networks. Fortunately {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://C7D57BC7-3979-4AF6-9892-659E203BE3C7"}}{\fldrslt the majority of people have seen little no change to their internet connection}}, despite increased usage. Unfortunately, as is all too frequently the case, the people hit hardest are those most in need.\
With families at home and competing for bandwidth for school, work and entertainment connections can slow to a crawl, even if the network as a whole is fine. For people on slower connections, either for financial reasons or because there is no alternative, these problems are exacerbated to the point that {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://03EBA389-23FB-4119-A2DB-949BB1F191B7"}}{\fldrslt it is impossible to be productive}}. In fact, the Children\'92s Commissioner estimates that 9% of families don\'92t even have an internet-connected device at home. To paraphrase the Children\'92s Commissioner, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://954B42AE-9AE6-4F72-8073-0C120496BE20"}}{\fldrslt having access is not the same as having 
